==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|vermillion}} (more at [[vermillion#Usage notes|vermillion § Usage notes]])

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|vermeillon||vermilion}}, from {{m|fro|vermeil}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|vermiculus||little worm}}, from {{m|la|vermis||worm}}, ultimately in reference to {{taxlink|Kermes vermilio|species|noshow=1}}, a type of scale insect used to make a crimson dye.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/vɜː(ɹ)ˈmɪl.jən/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪljən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[vivid]] [[red]] [[synthetic]] [[pigment]] made of [[mercury sulfide]].
# A vivid red or slightly [[orange]] [[colour]].
#: {{color panel|E34234}}
{{quote-Fanny Hill|part=3
|I, struggling faintly, could not help feeling what I could not grasp, a column of the whitest ivory, beautifully streak'd with blue veins, and carrying, fully uncapt, a head of the liveliest '''vermilion'''}}
# A type of [[red]] [[dye]] [[worn]] in the parting of the [[hair]] by [[married]] [[Hindu]] [[women]].
# The red skin of the lips or its border with the skin of the face.

